{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"db7aa1b6-8212-4625-aa10-29363900bf6e","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nMTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`. Instead the test executable accepts `--filter` directly, but the **syntax differs**:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` *(same)* |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `Category=Smoke` *(same)* |\n| `&` (AND) | `&` *(same)* |\n\nThe operators are mostly the same, **but you invoke it differently**.\n\n### 2. Invocation change\n\nWith `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, `dotnet test` passes filters through, but the escaping can break. The most reliable approach:\n\n```bash\n# Option A – via dotnet test (use -- to forward args)\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# Option B – run the test executable directly\ndotnet build\n./bin/Debug/net8.0/TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### Key gotcha\n\nWith MTP, `dotnet test --filter` (without `--`) tries to use VSTest filter translation, which often fails silently or matches nothing. The `--` separator tells `dotnet test` to pass the argument directly to the MTP test runner.\n\n### If `Category` trait isn't found\n\nxUnit v3 renamed some built-in trait handling. If `Category=Smoke` stops matching, use the trait name explicitly:\n\n```bash\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThis should still work because your code uses `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]`, which is preserved in v3. The filter key matches the trait name.\n\n**TL;DR** — Change your CI command to:\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f495c5bc-dd6c-44b1-8d5c-0df006e86e50","outputTokens":517,"requestId":"4C1A:1FB596:B1D47F:DC4CE4:6A012B01"},"id":"55abb971-995c-439c-9a5e-976d4797313e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:04:14.248Z","parentId":"503d819f-b7b1-46a3-97d3-c3fdc1effa78"}
